  "track_info": "Martinsville Speedway is a 0.526-mile (0.847 km) oval in Ridgeway, Virginia, shaped like a paperclip: two long flat straights linked by tight, heavily braked turns with 12 degrees of banking. Opened in 1947 by H. Clay Earles, it is the oldest active venue on the NASCAR calendar. The Virginia is for Racing Lovers 200 is round 2 of the 2026 NASCAR Whelen Modified Tour season and the tour's 41st visit to Martinsville since 1985. Racing here is always about patience, aggression and survival in traffic, where track position is critical and contact is frequent. The winner receives Martinsville's traditional grandfather clock trophy. The series qualifying lap record at this track belongs to Ryan Preece with an 18.607-second lap (101.768 mph) from April 2021, and the all-time win record in tour competition belongs to Mike Stefanik with five victories.",
